ack \n* Harper/Morang \n* Harper/Chalmers \n* Cadillac/Harper \n* Cadillac/Warren \n* Kercheval/McClellan\n* Larned/Chene \n* Rosa Parks Transit Center\n\n|| \n* Rosa Parks Transit Center\n* Larned/Chene\n* Kercheval/McClelland\n* Cadillac/Warren\n* Cadillac/Harper\n* Harper/Chalmers\n* Harper/Morang\n* Moross/Mack \n||\n*[https://detroitmi.gov/document/67-cadillacharper 67 Cadillac-Harper Schedule]\n|-\n| 68 Chalmers || \n* Waltham/8 Mile (check schedule Mon\u2013Fri only)\n* 7 Mile/Gratiot\n* Chalmers/Harper\n* Chalmers/Warren\n* Jefferson/Maryland\n|| \n* Jefferson/Maryland\n* Chalmers/Warren\n* Chalmers/Harper\n* 7 Mile/Gratiot\n* Waltham/8 Mile (check schedule Mon\u2013Fri only)\n||\n* [https://detroitmi.gov/document/68-chalmers 68 Chalmers Schedule]\n|-\n| 80 Villages Direct <br /><br /> (Mon\u2013Fri only) ||\n* Maryland/Jefferson\n* Jefferson/Cadillac\n* Lafayette/Van Dyke\n* Lafayette/Rivard\n* Canfield/Beaubien\n* W. Grand Blvd./M-10 (Lodge Fwy)\n||\n* W. Grand Blvd./Trumbull\n* Canfield/Beaubien\n* Lafayette/Rivard\n* Lafayette/Van Dyke\n* Jefferson/Cadillac\n* Maryland/Jefferson\n||\n* [https://detroitmi.gov/document/80-villages-direct 80 Villages Direct Schedule]\n|-\n| 89 Southwest Direct <br /><br /> (Mon\u2013Fri only) ||\n* Fort/Outer Drive\n* Springwells/Lafayette\n* Vernor/Livernois\n* Michigan/14th\n* Cass/Warren\n* W. Grand Blvd./M-10 (Lodge Fwy)\n||\n* W. Grand Blvd./Trumbull\n* Warren/Cass\n* Michigan/14th\n* Vernor/Livernois\n* Springwells/Lafayette\n* Fort/Outer Drive\n||\n* [https://detroitmi.gov/document/89-southwest-direct 89 Southwest Direct Schedule]\n|-\n| 92 Rosedale Express <br /><br /> (Mon\u2013Fri only) ||\n* Pembroke/Vaughan\n* Evergreen/Pembroke\n* Grand River/Evergreen\n* Grand River/Schaefer\n* Grand River/Times Square\n* Larned/St. Antoine\n||\n* Jefferson/St. Antoine\n* Michigan/Washington\n* Grand River/Schaefer\n* Evergreen/Grand River\n* Pembroke/Vaughan\n* Evergreen/Pembroke\n||\n* [https://detroitmi.gov/document/92-rosedale-express 92 Rosedale Express Schedule]\n|-\n| 95 Ryan Express <br /><br /> (Mon\u2013Fri only) ||\n* E. Outer Dr./Van Dyke\n* Ryan/Nevada\n* Conant/Caniff\n* Lumpkin/Holbrook\n* Gratiot/Beaubien\n* Congress/Washington\n||\n* Financial District People Mover\n* Brush/Madison\n* Lumpkin/Holbrook\n* Conant/Caniff\n* Ryan/Nevada\n* E. Outer Dr./Van Dyke\n||\n* [https://detroitmi.gov/document/95-ryan-express 95 Ryan Express Schedule]\n|-\n| 96 Joy Express <br /><br /> (Mon\u2013Fri only) ||\n* Evergreen/Capitol\n* Joy/Evergreen\n* Joy/Greenfield\n* Joy/Livernois\n* Grand River/Times Square\n* Larned/St. Antoine\n||\n* Jefferson/St. Antoine\n* Michigan/Washington\n* Joy/Livernois\n* Joy/Greenfield\n* Evergreen/Joy\n* Evergreen/Capitol\n||\n* [https://detroitmi.gov/document/96-joy-express 96 Joy Express Schedule]\n|}\n\n===Former Routes===\n*1 Downtown Get Around Green Loop (discontinued in 1997 and became part of an extended Route 3)\n*2 Downtown Get Around Red Loop (discontinued on April 23, 2005)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060925090301/http://www.ci.detroit.mi.us/mayor/releases/2005%20releases/DDOT%20Service%20Changes.htm}}</ref>\n*3 Baker-West Vernor (merged with Route 36 Oakland to form Route 90 Baker-Oakland on September 5, 1992; this section of Route became part of Route 49 on June 17, 1995)\n*3 Medical Center Shuttle (created in June 1996; rename Route 3 Cultural Attractions Trolley in  January 2003)\n*3 Cultural Attractions Trolley (discontinued on April 23, 2005)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060925090301/http://www.ci.detroit.mi.us/mayor/releases/2005%20releases/DDOT%20Service%20Changes.htm}}</ref>\n*4 Belle Isle (merged into Route 12 Conant, now 12 Conant-8 Mile in 1989; this section was discontinued on April 12, 2007)\n*4 Zoo Shuttle (Summer service only; created on February 1, 1997; discontinued in 2004)\n*5 Broadstreet (discontinued on September 6, 1988)\n*5 Ford Meadows Shuttle (created on February 1, 1997; discontinued on September 7, 2002)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20021018144219/http://www.ci.detroit.mi.us/ddot/ddotText/schedule_changes_sept.htm}}</ref>\n*6 Buchanan (discontinued on September 7, 2002)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20021018144219/http://www.ci.detroit.mi.us/ddot/ddotText/schedule_changes_sept.htm}}</ref>\n*7 Cadillac/Harper (renumbered Route 67 Cadillac/Harper on September 1, 2018 as part of ConnectTen)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180831034436/http://www.detroitmi.gov/Government/Departments-and-Agencies/Detroit-Department-of-Transportation/DDOT-News-and-Alerts/ArticleID/2369/Final-Service-Change-Meetings}}</ref>\n*8 Caniff (merged into Route 38 Plymouth to form Route 38 Plymouth-Caniff on June 25, 2011; Route 38 service to Downtown was discontinued)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110813052052/http://www.detroitmi.gov/Portals/0/docs/deptoftransportation/pdfs/2011/Service_Change_Booklet_For_June_2011.pdf}}</ref>\n*9 Chalmers (renumbered Route 68 Chalmers on September 1, 2018 as part of ConnectTen)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180831034436/http://www.detroitmi.gov/Government/Departments-and-Agencies/Detroit-Department-of-Transportation/DDOT-News-and-Alerts/ArticleID/2369/Final-Service-Change-Meetings}}</ref>\n*10 Chene (renumbered Route 52 Chene on September 1, 2018 as part of ConnectTen)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180831034436/http://www.detroitmi.gov/Government/Departments-and-Agencies/Detroit-Department-of-Transportation/DDOT-News-and-Alerts/ArticleID/2369/Final-Service-Change-Meetings}}</ref>\n*14 Crosstown (renumbered and renamed Route 8 Warren on September 1, 2018 as part of ConnectTen)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180831034436/http://www.detroitmi.gov/Government/Departments-and-Agencies/Detroit-Department-of-Transportation/DDOT-News-and-Alerts/ArticleID/2369/Final-Service-Change-Meetings}}</ref>\n*20 Grand Belt (discontinued on September 26, 2009)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100717194120/http://www.detroitmi.gov/Portals/0/docs/deptoftransportation/pdfs/Service_Changes_September_2009.pdf}}</ref>\n*21 Grand River (renumbered Route 3 Grand River on September 1, 2018 as part of ConnectTen)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180831034436/http://www.detroitmi.gov/Government/Departments-and-Agencies/Detroit-Department-of-Transportation/DDOT-News-and-Alerts/ArticleID/2369/Final-Service-Change-Meetings}}</ref>\n*22 Greenfield (renumbered Route 10 Greenfield on September 1, 2018 as part of ConnectTen)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180831034436/http://www.detroitmi.gov/Government/Departments-and-Agencies/Detroit-Department-of-Transportation/DDOT-News-and-Alerts/ArticleID/2369/Final-Service-Change-Meetings}}</ref>\n*24 Holbrook (discontinued on September 26, 2009)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100717194120/http://www.detroitmi.gov/Portals/0/docs/deptoftransportation/pdfs/Service_Changes_September_2009.pdf}}</ref>\n*25 Jefferson (renumbered Route 9 Jefferson on September 1, 2018 as part of ConnectTen)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180831034436/http://www.detroitmi.gov/Government/Departments-and-Agencies/Detroit-Department-of-Transportation/DDOT-News-and-Alerts/ArticleID/2369/Final-Service-Change-Meetings}}</ref>\n*26 John R. North (discontinued on September 6, 1988; duplicated SMART Route 495)\n*26 Greenfield Spinner (created on February 1, 1997; discontinued on January 17, 1998)\n*28 Lafayette-Green (discontinued on April 23, 2005)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060925090301/http://www.ci.detroit.mi.us/mayor/releases/2005%20releases/DDOT%20Service%20Changes.htm}}</ref>\n*33 Meyers-Northlawn (discontinued on September 6, 1988)\n*33 John R. Limited (created on February 1, 1997; discontinued on January 17, 1998; restored on August 23, 2003; discontinued on April 23, 2005)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20040411060946/http://www.ci.detroit.mi.us/ddot/ddotText/schedule_changes_aug03.htm}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060925090301/http://www.ci.detroit.mi.us/mayor/releases/2005%20releases/DDOT%20Service%20Changes.htm}}</ref>\n*34 Gratiot (renumbered Route 6 Gratiot on September 1, 2018 as part of ConnectTen)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180831034436/http://www.detroitmi.gov/Government/Departments-and-Agencies/Detroit-Department-of-Transportation/DDOT-News-and-Alerts/ArticleID/2369/Final-Service-Change-Meetings}}</ref>\n*35 Mount Elliott (discontinued on September 6, 1988)\n*35 Meyers (created on March 6, 1999; discontinued on April 23, 2005)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060925090301/http://www.ci.detroit.mi.us/mayor/releases/2005%20releases/DDOT%20Service%20Changes.htm}}</ref>\n*36 Oakland (merged with Route 3 Baker-West Vernor to form 90 Baker-Oakland on September 5, 1992; restored on June 17, 1995 when Route 90 was split, discontinued on February 8, 2014 and split into Route 43 Schoolcraft and Route 49 Vernor (now Route 1 Vernor))\n*37 Michigan (renumbered Route 2 Michigan on September 1, 2018 as part of ConnectTen)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180831034436/http://www.detroitmi.gov/Government/Departments-and-Agencies/Detroit-Department-of-Transportation/DDOT-News-and-Alerts/ArticleID/2369/Final-Service-Change-Meetings}}</ref>\n*42 Schoenherr-Redmond (discontinued on September 6, 1988; current Route 42 created in April 2017)\n*44 Second Boulevard (discontinued on June 25, 1994)\n*45 Seven Mile (renumbered Route 7 Seven Mile on September 1, 2018 as part of ConnectTen)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180831034436/http://www.detroitmi.gov/Government/Departments-and-Agencies/Detroit-Department-of-Transportation/DDOT-News-and-Alerts/ArticleID/2369/Final-Service-Change-Meetings}}</ref>\n*48 Van Dyke/Lafayette (renumbered Route 5 Van Dyke/Lafayette on September 1, 2018 as part of ConnectTen)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180831034436/http://www.detroitmi.gov/Government/Departments-and-Agencies/Detroit-Department-of-Transportation/DDOT-News-and-Alerts/ArticleID/2369/Final-Service-Change-Meetings}}</ref>\n*49 East Vernor (merged with Route 27 Joy to form Route 96 Joy-Vernor on September 5, 1992\n*49 Vernor (created on June 17, 1995 replacing the West Vernor portion of Route 90 and the east Vernor portion of Route 96; renumbered Route 1 Vernor on September 1, 2018 as part of ConnectTen)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180831034436/http://www.detroitmi.gov/Government/Departments-and-Agencies/Detroit-Department-of-Transportation/DDOT-News-and-Alerts/ArticleID/2369/Final-Service-Change-Meetings}}</ref>\n*50 Warren East (merged into Route 14 Crosstown, now Route 8 Warren)\n*51 West Jefferson (discontinued on September 6, 1988 with portions transferred to Route 30)\n*52 Woodrow Wilson (discontinued on April 23, 2005)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060925090301/http://www.ci.detroit.mi.us/mayor/releases/2005%20releases/DDOT%20Service%20Changes.htm}}</ref>\n*53 Woodward (renumbered Route 4 Woodward on September 1, 2018 as part of ConnectTen)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180831034436/http://www.detroitmi.gov/Government/Departments-and-Agencies/Detroit-Department-of-Transportation/DDOT-News-and-Alerts/ArticleID/2369/Final-Service-Change-Meetings}}</ref>\n*53 Woodward-John R. (created on June 27, 1994 when Route 53 Woodward (which was part of Route 97 for a short time before that) merged with Route 495 John R. (a SMART route that DDOT took over operation of) to form this route; resplit on April 1, 1995 when SMART took over operation of Route 495)\n*66 Downtown Lunch Time Express (created on June 27, 1994; discontinued on September 6, 1995)\n*70 Cadillac-Harper Express (discontinued on September 6, 1988)\n*70 Crosstown Express (discontinued on April 23, 2005; restored on June 16, 2008, but discontinued again on April 18, 2009)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080630070540/http://www.ci.detroit.mi.us/Departments/DetroitDepartmentofTransportation/BusInformation/ExpressService/tabid/2071/Default.aspx}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090408014640/http://www.detroitmi.gov/Portals/0/docs/deptoftransportation/pdfs/promos/ddot_routemodifications042009.pdf}}</ref>\n*71 Grand River Express (created on June 16, 2008; discontinued on April 18, 2009)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080630070540/http://www.ci.detroit.mi.us/Departments/DetroitDepartmentofTransportation/BusInformation/ExpressService/tabid/2071/Default.aspx}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090408014640/http://www.detroitmi.gov/Portals/0/docs/deptoftransportation/pdfs/promos/ddot_routemodifications042009.pdf}}</ref>\n*71 Crosstown Express (discontinued circa 1988; restored as Route 70 later that year)\n*72 Dexter Express (discontinued on April 23, 2005; restored on June 16, 2008, but discontinued again on April 18, 2009)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080630070540/http://www.ci.detroit.mi.us/Departments/DetroitDepartmentofTransportation/BusInformation/ExpressService/tabid/2071/Default.aspx}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090408014640/http://www.detroitmi.gov/Portals/0/docs/deptoftransportation/pdfs/promos/ddot_routemodifications042009.pdf}}</ref>\n*73 Fenkell Express (discontinued circa 1988)\n*73 Woodward Express  (created on June 16, 2008; discontinued on April 18, 2009)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080630070540/http://www.ci.detroit.mi.us/Departments/DetroitDepartmentofTransportation/BusInformation/ExpressService/tabid/2071/Default.aspx}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090408014640/http://www.detroitmi.gov/Portals/0/docs/deptoftransportation/pdfs/promos/ddot_routemodifications042009.pdf}}</ref>\n*74 Grand River Express (discontinued circa 1988; restored as Route 71 on June 16, 2008)\n*74 Gratiot Express  (created on June 16, 2008; discontinued on April 18, 2009)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080630070540/http://www.ci.detroit.mi.us/Departments/DetroitDepartmentofTransportation/BusInformation/ExpressService/tabid/2071/Default.aspx}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090408014640/http://www.detroitmi.gov/Portals/0/docs/deptoftransportation/pdfs/promos/ddot_routemodifications042009.pdf}}</ref>\n*75 Gratiot Express (discontinued circa 1988; restored as Route 74 on June 16, 2008)\n*76 Hayes Limited (discontinued on June 25, 2011)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110813052052/http://www.detroitmi.gov/Portals/0/docs/deptoftransportation/pdfs/2011/Service_Change_Booklet_For_June_2011.pdf}}</ref>\n*77 Hamilton Express (discontinued circa 1988)\n*78 Imperial Limited (discontinued on March 3, 2012; Route 49 Vernor (now Route 1 Vernor) lost its eastern section that day)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120306041922/http://www.detroitmi.gov/Portals/0/docs/deptoftransportation/pdfs/Service_Changes_March_Weekday_2012.pdf}}</ref>\n*79 Jefferson Express (discontinued circa 1988)\n*80 Joy Road Express (discontinued circa 1988)\n*80 Hayes Flex (created on February 1, 1997; discontinued on September 7, 2002)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20021018144219/http://www.ci.detroit.mi.us/ddot/ddotText/schedule_changes_sept.htm}}</ref>\n*81 Oakland Express (discontinued circa 1988)\n*82 Plymouth Express (discontinued circa 1988)\n*83 Rouge Express (discontinued circa 1988)\n*84 Schoolcraft Express (discontinued circa 1988)\n*85 West McNichols Express (discontinued circa 1988)\n*86 Van Dyke Express (discontinued circa 1988)\n*87 Vernor-Mack Express (discontinued circa 1988)\n*88 Woodward Express (discontinued circa 1988; restored as Route 73 on June 16, 2008)\n*90 Baker-Oakland (created on September 5, 1992 as a merge of Route 3 Baker-West Vernor and 36 Oakland; resplit on June 17, 1995 into part of Route 49 Vernor (now Route 1 Vernor) and Route 36 Oakland)\n*93 Gratiot-Michigan (created on September 5, 1992 as a merge of Route 34 Gratiot and Route 37 Michigan; resplit on June 25, 1994 when SMART took over operation of Route 37)\n*94 VA Park & Ride (created on February 1, 1997; discontinued on January 17, 1998)\n*95 Woodmere Shuttle (discontinued on March 14, 1973)\n*96 Joy-Vernor (created on September 5, 1992 as a merge of Route 27 Joy and Route 49 East Vernor; resplit on June 17, 1995 into Route 27 Joy and Route 49 Vernor)\n*97 Woodward-Jefferson (created on September 5, 1992 as a merge of Route 25 Jefferson and Route 53 Woodward; resplit on June 25, 1994 when SMART took over operation of Route 25, while DDOT took over operation of Route 495, which merged with Route 53 Woodward to form Route 53 Woodward-John R.)\n*99 Lahser (Discontinued on April 23, 2005)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060925090301/http://www.ci.detroit.mi.us/mayor/releases/2005%20releases/DDOT%20Service%20Changes.htm}}</ref>\n*101 Hubbell Spinner (discontinued in the mid-1990s; the 101 number was on rollsigns, but was most likely never officially used)\n*125 Fort Street-Detroit (SMART route operated by DDOT from June 27, 1994 to April 1, 1995; at the time, Routes 25 and 37 were operated by SMART)\n*150 Taylor-Detroit (SMART route operated by DDOT from June 27, 1994 to April 1, 1995; SMART discontinued the route completely on December 12, 2011)\n\n==Fleet==\n\n===Current Fleet=== \n<ref>{{cite web|title=Detroit Transit History Roster|url=http://www.detroittransithistory.info/Roster/DDOT-active.html|website=detroittransithistory.info}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year || Make || Model || Length || Capacity || Propulsion || Engine || Fleet Series || Quantity\n|-\n|2003 || [[New Flyer]] || D40LF || 40 || 39 || [[