tes operate hourly on Mondays through Saturdays and the fare is $5.00.\n\n==Fleet==\n\n* 56 standard buses\n* 43 Orion VII CNG LF buses\n* 10 CNG \"vintage trolleys\" (trolley-replica buses)\n* 22 paratransit buses\n\n==References==\n* [https://www.bjcta.org/about-us/bjcta-history/ bjcta.org Historical]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20060615031909/http://www.bjcta.org/index.php?id=173 About Us] \n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20100611235004/http://www.bjcta.org/news/fstatements/FY%202009%20Budget.pdf BJCTA 2009 Capital and Operating Budget]\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.bjcta.org/ Birmingham-Jefferson County Transit Authority homepage]\n* http://qcaclients.com/maxwebsite/{{dead link|date=November 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n\n[[Category:Transit agencies in Alabama]]\n[[Category:Bus transportation in Alabama]]\n[[Category:Government agencies established in 1972]]\n[[Category:Transit authorities with natural gas buses]]\n", "name_user": "2602:30a:c043:79a0:1961:32c8:5e56:fd3e", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eFare prices:All fares are free since mid-March.)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Birmingham-Jefferson_County_Transit_Authority"}
